HEADWORD: Resettlement
<hw>Re*set"tle*ment</hw> <pr>(-m<it>e</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>Act of settling again, or state of being settled again; <as>as, the
<ex>resettlement</ex> of lees</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>resettlement</qex> of my discomposed soul.</q>
<rj><qau>Norris.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reshape</ent>⟦br⟧
